.TH "drm_gem_vram_simple_display_pipe_prepare_fb" 9 "drm_gem_vram_simple_display_pipe_prepare_fb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_vram_simple_display_pipe_prepare_fb \- * Implements &struct drm_simple_display_pipe_funcs.prepare_fb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_gem_vram_simple_display_pipe_prepare_fb
.BI "(struct drm_simple_display_pipe *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct drm_plane_state *new_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
a simple display pipe
.IP "new_state" 12
the plane's new state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
During plane updates, this function pins the GEM VRAM
objects of the plane's new framebuffer to VRAM. Call
\fBdrm_gem_vram_simple_display_pipe_cleanup_fb\fP to unpin them.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or
a negative errno code otherwise.
